summary:
Tony Stark was raised specifically to be blind to the problematic aspects of Stark Industries. 
He was worked and groomed into...
body:
Tony Stark was raised specifically to be blind to the problematic aspects of Stark Industries.

He was worked and groomed into an easily manipulated puppet by those around him(why wouldn’t he trust Obie?)

Then the moment he realized he had been wrong he reavaluated and changed, not only his own behavior, but the behavior of his company as well.

I think the scene that best puts this into perspective is when he goes back to Afghanistan. He destroys the weapons that give the 10 rings the edge, and then (this is incredibly important) he gives the leader to the people so they can decide what justice looks like.

Tony isn’t judge jury and executioner, he’s an equalizer.

That’s what makes him so special. That’s why hes a hero.

Yall can call him an imperialist, a war profiteering monster, egotistical and dangerous all you want.

But that just means we know you missed the biggest character arc in the MCU

Livin' the Fandom Life, Philly Style.
Fandoms, real life, and everything in between.

I post a little bit of every thing, quotes, jokes, sports (teams are USMNT, Philadelphia Union, Philadelphia Eagles, Auburn Tigers), and fandoms including Dragon Age, Sailor Moon, The Hunger Games, Marvel, Knights of the Old Republic, Harry Potter, Star Wars, Lord of the Rings, Gone with the Wind, old school Cartoon Network, Disney, and who knows what else.

I also have a sideblog where I post my Dragon Age fanfics and drabbles over at mabarisareagirlsbestfriend.tumblr.com

Got a question? My inbox is always open, even when school has knocked me down and is kicking me in the teeth.
